members.name: clickValidator
constrainTo
members.doc:
Initializes the drag drop object's constraints to restrict movement to a certain element.

Usage:

var dd = new Ext.dd.DDProxy("dragDiv1", "proxytest",
               { dragElId: "existingProxyDiv" });
dd.startDrag = function(){
    this.constrainTo("parent-id");
};

Or you can initalize it using the Ext.dom.Element object:

Ext.get("dragDiv1").initDDProxy("proxytest", {dragElId: "existingProxyDiv"}, {
    startDrag : function(){
        this.constrainTo("parent-id");
    }
});

params.name: constrainTo
params.doc: The element or element ID to constrain to.

params.name: pad
params.doc: Pad provides a way to specify "padding" of the constraints, and can be either a number for symmetrical padding (4 would be equal to {left:4, right:4, top:4, bottom:4}) or an object containing the sides to pad. For example: {right:10, bottom:10}

params.name: inContent
params.doc: Constrain the draggable in the content box of the element (inside padding and borders)

members.short_doc: Initializes the drag drop object's constraints to restrict movement to a certain element. ...

members.name: notifyDrop
members.doc: The function a Ext.dd.DragSource calls once to notify this drop zone that the dragged item has been dropped on it. The drag zone will look up the target node based on the event passed in, and if there is a node registered for that event, it will delegate to onNodeDrop for node-specific handling, otherwise it will call onContainerDrop.

params.name: source
params.doc: The drag source that was dragged over this drop zone

params.name: data
params.doc: An object containing arbitrary data supplied by the drag source

members.short_doc:
The function a Ext.dd.DragSource calls once to notify this drop zone that the dragged item has
been dropped on it. ...

members.name: notifyEnter
members.doc: The function a Ext.dd.DragSource calls once to notify this drop zone that the source is now over the zone. The default implementation returns this.dropNotAllowed and expects that only registered drop nodes can process drag drop operations, so if you need the drop zone itself to be able to process drops you should override this method and provide a custom implementation.

params.name: source
params.doc: The drag source that was dragged over this drop zone

params.name: data
params.doc: An object containing arbitrary data supplied by the drag source

return.name: return
return.doc: status The CSS class that communicates the drop status back to the source so that the underlying Ext.dd.StatusProxy can be updated

members.short_doc:

the zone. ...

members.name: notifyOver
members.doc: The function a Ext.dd.DragSource calls continuously while it is being dragged over the drop zone. This method will be called on every mouse movement while the drag source is over the drop zone. It will call onNodeOver while the drag source is over a registered node, and will also automatically delegate to the appropriate node-specific methods as necessary when the drag source enters and exits registered nodes (onNodeEnter, onNodeOut). If the drag source is not currently over a registered node, it will call onContainerOver.

params.name: source
params.doc: The drag source that was dragged over this drop zone

params.name: data
params.doc: An object containing arbitrary data supplied by the drag source

return.name: return
return.doc: status The CSS class that communicates the drop status back to the source so that the underlying Ext.dd.StatusProxy can be updated

members.short_doc: The function a Ext.dd.DragSource calls continuously while it is being dragged over the drop zone. ...

members.name: onContainerDrop
members.doc: Called when the DropZone determines that a Ext.dd.DragSource has been dropped on it, but not on any of its registered drop nodes. The default implementation returns false, so it should be overridden to provide the appropriate processing of the drop event if you need the drop zone itself to be able to accept drops. It should return true when valid so that the drag source's repair action does not run.

return.name: return
return.doc: True if the drop was valid, else false
